				%section
					.lecturer Paul Ursell
					.title Consultant Ophthalmologist
					.place Epsom and St Helier NHS Trust
					%p Mr Paul Unsell is a consultant opthalmologist at Epsom and St Helier NHS Trust. He graduated from St Maryís in London and wrote his MD thesis at St Thomasí Hospital on cataract surgery. He was a clinical lecturer in opthalmology in Oxford for 5 years and then spent a yearís fellowship at the Lionís Institute in Western Australia specialising in advanced cataract and refractive surgery. His specialist interest is in advanced cataract and refractive surgery and he is in demand as a guest speaker at many international meetings.

				%section
					.lecturer David Clough
					.title Charles Rippin and Turner Accountants
					%p David Clough is a partner in Charles Rippin and Turner who specialise in dealing with medical accounts, especially those of General Practitioners. David is the Chairman of Association of Independent Specialist Medical Accountants (aisma) and writes regularly for Doctor Magazine, in addition to lecturing to General Practitioners and GP Registrars.

				%section
					.lecturer Prof Matt Thompson
					.title Professor in Vascular Surgery 
					.place St George's Hospital NHS Trust
					%p Matt Thompson qualified from St Bartholomewís Hospital and trained in vascular surgery at Leicester Royal Infirmary and Queen Elizabeth Hospital in Adelaide. He trained in research techniques as a Wellcome Fellow, and has longstanding research interests into the treatment of abdominal aortic aneurysms. He has over 100 peer-reviewed publications. His clinical interests are in all aspects of Vascular Surgery, including arterial and venous disease. Specialised interests include minimally invasive Vascular Surgery and the treatment of complex aneurysm disease.

